canbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The view finder configuration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes it is necessary to limit a live video frame detection or recognition to a certain rectangular area with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, to guide the user, the view finder visualizes the region of interest by drawing a rectangle around"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the user interface."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@objcMembers"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since the display resp. the camera view size differs from device to device specifying the region of interest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in absolute screen points would require some additional calculations and therefore be inconvenient."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Instead a combination of aspect ratio and minimum distances to the view(screen) edges is used."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata"